## Deploy Steps (10-step process)

1. Teardown existing virtual app + app pool
2. Install files from staging (`Install-OurWinApp`)
3. Create app pool (set identity)
4. Create virtual application under Default Web Site
5. Verify/generate web.config (sets `ASPNETCORE_URLS`, `maxQueryString=8192`)
6. Set folder permissions (ReadAndExecute for app pool identity)
7. Create firewall rules (inbound + outbound for ApiPort)
8. Start app pool
9. Verify (app pool started, site started, virtual app exists)
10. Health check (HTTP GET to HealthEndpoint)

## IIS-RedeployAll Phases

1. **UNINSTALL** — remove all virtual apps (apps first, root site last)
2. **IIS RESET** — `iisreset /restart`
3. **DEPLOY** — deploy root site first, then all apps from templates

